    <div class="container">
        <header>
            <h1>JarsMaster</h1>
            <p style="font-size: 1.25rem; color: #4B5563; margin-top: 0;">Privacy Policy</p>
            <p class="last-updated">Last Updated: 06/02/2026</p>
        </header>

        <article>
            <p>Welcome to <strong>JarsMaster</strong>. We are committed to protecting your personal information and
                respecting your privacy. This policy explains how we collect, use, and safeguard your data when you use
                the JarsMaster application.</p>

            <h2>1. Data We Collect</h2>
            <p>JarsMaster operates on the principle "Your data belongs to you". We collect only the minimum information
                necessary for the app to function:</p>
            <ul>
                <li><strong>Account Information (Optional):</strong> When you enable Cloud Sync, we use your Google
                    Account (Google Sign-In) for authentication. We only store your User ID and Email to identify your
                    data on the system.</li>
                <li><strong>Financial Data:</strong> Transaction records, jar balances (NECC, PLAY, FFA, etc.), and
                    asset/liability data. This data is stored <strong>locally on your device</strong> and is only
                    uploaded to our secure Cloud server if you *actively* enable synchronization.</li>
                <li><strong>Usage Data:</strong> Anonymous information about how you use the app (e.g., frequency of
                    opening the app, crash reports) via Google Firebase Analytics to help us improve product quality.
                </li>
                <li><strong>Advertising Identifiers:</strong> If you use the free version, Google AdMob may use your
                    device's advertising ID to serve relevant ads (unless you have disabled this in your device
                    settings).</li>
            </ul>

            <h2>2. How We Use Data</h2>
            <p>We use the collected information to:</p>
            <ul>
                <li>Provide core features: Expense management using the 6 Jars Method.</li>
                <li>Synchronize data across your devices (if enabled).</li>
                <li>Provide intelligent financial analysis (via integrated AI).</li>
                <li>Detect and fix application errors.</li>
            </ul>
            <p><strong>We DO NOT sell your personal data to any third parties.</strong></p>

            <h2>3. Device Permissions</h2>
            <p>To function fully, JarsMaster may request access to:</p>
            <ul>
                <li><strong>Internet:</strong> To synchronize data and download resources (Themes, updates).</li>
                <li><strong>Biometrics (Fingerprint/FaceID):</strong> To provide the secure App Lock feature. Biometric
                    data is processed only by the OS and we never store it.</li>
                <li><strong>Storage:</strong> To export Excel/JSON reports or save screenshots upon your request.</li>
            </ul>

            <h2>4. Data Security</h2>
            <p>We apply strict security standards:</p>
            <ul>
                <li>All data transmitted between your device and Cloud servers is encrypted using HTTPS/TLS protocols.
                </li>
                <li>Data on Cloud servers (Google Firebase) is protected by strict Security Rules, ensuring only you
                    have access to your data.</li>
                <li>PIN codes and security settings are stored securely on your device.</li>
            </ul>

            <h2>5. Third-Party Services</h2>
            <p>The application uses trusted third-party services for operation:</p>
            <ul>
                <li><strong>Google Firebase:</strong> User authentication, database storage, and crash analytics.</li>
                <li><strong>Google AdMob:</strong> Ad serving (in the free version).</li>
                <li><strong>Google Gemini AI:</strong> Supports financial data analysis (data sent is valid for the
                    session only and used strictly for analysis).</li>
            </ul>

            <h2>6. Your Rights</h2>
            <p>You have full control over your data:</p>
            <ul>
                <li><strong>Access & Edit:</strong> You can view and modify all financial data directly within the app.
                </li>
                <li><strong>Delete Account:</strong> You can request permanent deletion of your account and all related
                    data at any time via "Settings > Account > Delete Account" in the app.</li>
                <li><strong>Disable Sync:</strong> You can choose to use the app in Offline Mode (Data stored only on
                    device).</li>
            </ul>

            <h2>7. Contact Us</h2>
            <p>If you have any questions about this Privacy Policy, please contact us at:</p>
